events.1913: Canberra is selected as the site for the new capital of Australia.
events.1927: Canberra officially becomes the capital of Australia and the Parliament House is opened.
events.1940: Construction of the Australian War Memorial begins in Canberra.
events.1951: The National Library of Australia is established in Canberra.
events.1963: Lake Burley Griffin, the central feature of Canberra, is completed.
events.1974: The completion of the new Parliament House in Canberra.
events.1988: Canberra celebrates its 75th anniversary as the capital of Australia with the opening of the National Gallery of Australia.
events.2003: The Canberra bushfires devastate parts of the city and surrounding areas.
events.2013: Canberra celebrates its centenary with various events and festivities.
events.2020: COVID-19 pandemic impacts Canberra, leading to lockdowns and changes in daily life.
